should—become so.Identifying constraints such as an inflexible constitution, inherent antimilitarism, and its position as a U.S. security client, Japan as a 'Normal Country'? goes on to analyse factors that could make Japan a more effective regional and global player. These essays ultimately consider how Japan could leverage its considerable human, cultural, technological, and financial capital to benefit both its citizens and the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aEr Lam, Peng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHee Park, Cheol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoeya, Yoshihide , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSoeya, Yoshihide, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwenson-Wright, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTadokoro, Masayaki, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTadokoro, Masayuki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWang, Jianwei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWelch, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWelch, David A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442694231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442694231.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK